parameters.name: BR
parameters.description:
KRTP radial (r) component of the magnetic-field in nT.                  
      R is along the Saturn to spacecraft line, positive away from Saturn.

parameters.name: BTHETA
parameters.description:
KRTP southward (theta) component of the magnetic-field in nT.           
      Theta completes the right handed set (Phi x R) and is positive          
      southward.

parameters.name: BPHI
parameters.description:
KRTP azimuthal (phi) component of the magnetic-field in nT.             
      Phi is parallel to Saturn's equator (Omega x R), perpendicular to       
      the Saturn-spacecraft line, and positive in the direction of            
      corotation.

parameters.name: BTOTAL
parameters.description:
Average value of the full-resolution magnetic-field magnitudes          
      calculated over the averaging interval in nT. Note that this value      
      may differ slightly from the square root of the sum of the squares      
      of the averaged field components.

parameters.name: NPTS
parameters.description: Number of points in the average.
